<subSubSection id="C3266556D361FFC6FF17F92BDB27F854" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD361FFC6FF17F92BDB27F854" blockId="2.[151,1437,1640,2027]" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD361FFC6FF17F92BDFFBF8E4" bold="true" box="[199,436,1784,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Diagnosis of female.</emphasis>
Compared to male (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B2CD361FFC6FD46F92BDD7CF8E4" author="Bucsek, K." box="[662,819,1784,1810]" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" refId="ref6390" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malaya Peninsula-Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek, 2012</bibRefCitation>
: pl. 16: 236), the female is more dark gray ground color of forewing and has slightly broader medial dark band in forewing (
<figureCitation id="13072A58D361FFC6FC54F8CFDD8EF8C0" box="[900,961,1820,1846]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,191,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[163,1424,181,1787]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. General view of the body of adults of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 2. S. fractilinea, female (INU˗10364T). 3. S. gemina, male (INU˗10356T). 4. S. mlcochi, male (INU˗10355T). 5a. S. pectenicorniculum, male (OPU˗009T). 5b. ditto, female (OPU˗008T). 6a. S. fuscus, male (OPU˗001T). 6b. ditto, female (OPU˗017T). 7a. S. cambodiensis, male (INU˗10358T). 7b. ditto, female (INU˗10362T). 8a. S. bokorensis, male (OPU˗014T). 8b. ditto, female (OPU˗018M). 9. S. kualabohi, female (INU˗10351T). 10. S. transversana, male (OPU˗015T). 11a. S. trigonica sp. n., male (holotype, INU˗10363T). 11b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗10353T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571783/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Fig 9</figureCitation>
). The female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED361FFC6FB0CF8CFDB27F8C0" authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2012" box="[1244,1384,1820,1846]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kualabohi">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD361FFC6FB0CF8CFDB27F8C0" box="[1244,1384,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">S. kualabohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D361FFC6FAA5F8CFDEFBF8AD" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1374,1398]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,195,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1436,181,1350]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. Female genitalia of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 20. S. fractilinea (INU˗10364T). 21. S. pectenicorniculum (OPU˗008T). 22. S. fuscus (OPU˗011T). 23. S. bokorensis (OPU˗018Malaysia). 24. S. trigonica sp. n. (paratype, INU˗10353T). 25. S. kualabohi (INU˗10351T). 26. S. cambodiensis (INU˗10362T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571787/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Fig 25</figureCitation>
) differ from other members of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED361FFC6FDC7F893DC3EF8AC" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1900" box="[535,625,1856,1882]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD361FFC6FDC7F893DC3EF8AC" box="[535,625,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Stictane</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the funnel shaped ostium; broad tubular ductus bursae with strongly sclerotized longitudinal spurs in both lateral side, as long as bursae; significantly ovoid appendix bursae with three bundles of large spines, and globular, weakly wrinkled corpus bursae dense spinulose scobination near cervix.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266556D361FFC7FF17F87FDA81FE7F" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="484" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD361FFC7FF17F87FDA81FE7F" blockId="2.[151,1437,1640,2027]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,502]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="484" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD361FFC6FF17F87FDF9EF830" bold="true" box="[199,465,1964,1990]" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Description of female.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B948EACFD361FFC6FE09F87FDC59F830" box="[473,534,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D361FFC6FDF6F87FDC2AF830" box="[550,613,1964,1990]" captionStart="FIGURES 2–11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1810,1834]" captionTargetBox="[173,1415,191,1783]" captionTargetId="figure-23@4.[163,1424,181,1787]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 2–11. General view of the body of adults of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 2. S. fractilinea, female (INU˗10364T). 3. S. gemina, male (INU˗10356T). 4. S. mlcochi, male (INU˗10355T). 5a. S. pectenicorniculum, male (OPU˗009T). 5b. ditto, female (OPU˗008T). 6a. S. fuscus, male (OPU˗001T). 6b. ditto, female (OPU˗017T). 7a. S. cambodiensis, male (INU˗10358T). 7b. ditto, female (INU˗10362T). 8a. S. bokorensis, male (OPU˗014T). 8b. ditto, female (OPU˗018M). 9. S. kualabohi, female (INU˗10351T). 10. S. transversana, male (OPU˗015T). 11a. S. trigonica sp. n., male (holotype, INU˗10363T). 11b. ditto, female (paratype, INU˗10353T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571783" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571783/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="483">Fig 9</figureCitation>
). Length of forewing 
<quantity id="4CC49B38D361FFC6FCB2F87FDDE7F831" box="[866,936,1964,1991]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="483" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
. Head broken for examined sample. Thorax dark brown. Ground color of forewing dark brown-gray; basal area of forewing darker than ground color; antemedian series of two dark spots distinct; broad dark brown medial band almost straight, its more widened in costal margin; a distinct discoidal dot dark brown; postdiscal series of small dark spots distinct, its merged into apical dark brown patch. Hindwing paler than forewing, with sprinkled brown apex. 
<emphasis id="B948EACFD360FFC7FC18FF0CDAC9FF0F" box="[968,1158,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="13072A58D360FFC7FB45FF0CDAADFF0F" box="[1173,1250,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1374,1398]" captionTargetBox="[161,1426,195,1336]" captionTargetId="figure-23@6.[151,1436,181,1350]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–26. Female genitalia of the genus Stictane from Thailand. 20. S. fractilinea (INU˗10364T). 21. S. pectenicorniculum (OPU˗008T). 22. S. fuscus (OPU˗011T). 23. S. bokorensis (OPU˗018Malaysia). 24. S. trigonica sp. n. (paratype, INU˗10353T). 25. S. kualabohi (INU˗10351T). 26. S. cambodiensis (INU˗10362T)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6571787" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6571787/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Fig 25</figureCitation>
). Papillae anales weakly sclerotized. Apophyses posteriores and anteriores slender, same length. Triangular ostium weakly sclerotized. Ductus bursae tubular, weakly sclerotized, with strongly sclerotized longitudinal spurs in both lateral side, as long as bursae. Corpus bursae globular, weakly wrinkled and sclerotized, with dense spinulose scobination near cervix. Irregularly ovoid appendix bursae weakly sclerotized, with three bundles of large spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266556D360FFC7FF17FE41DD20FE5B" box="[199,879,402,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD360FFC7FF17FE41DD20FE5B" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,502]" box="[199,879,402,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD360FFC7FF17FE41DF2EFE5A" bold="true" box="[199,353,402,428]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F32B764DD360FFC7FEB7FE40DF82FE5B" box="[359,461,403,429]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Thailand</collectingCountry>
, Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F32B764DD360FFC7FD86FE40DCF2FE5B" box="[598,701,403,429]" name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B2CD360FFC7FD1BFE40DD2CFE5B" author="Bucsek, K." box="[715,867,403,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" refId="ref6390" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malaya Peninsula-Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3266556D360FFC7FF17FE64DBDCFE03" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8336DDD360FFC7FF17FE64DBDCFE03" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,502]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD360FFC7FF17FE64DF74FE27" bold="true" box="[199,315,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED360FFC7FE92FE64DF82FE27" authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2012" box="[322,461,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kualabohi">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD360FFC7FE92FE64DF82FE27" box="[322,461,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">S. kualabohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described for 
<specimenCount id="9D3AFD54D360FFC7FD4EFE64DD4CFE27" box="[670,771,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAD4B2CD360FFC7FCFCFE64DD9FFE27" author="Bucsek, K." box="[812,976,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" refId="ref6390" refString="Bucsek, K. (2012) Erebidae, Arctiinae (Lithosiini, Arctiini) of Malaya Peninsula-Malaysia. Institute of Zoology SAS, Bratislava, 170 pp." type="book" year="2012">Bucsek (2012)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F32B764DD360FFC7FBC3FE64DA32FE27" box="[1043,1149,439,465]" name="Malaysia" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. In this study, this species is newly recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F32B764DD360FFC7FE51FE08DFAAFE03" box="[385,485,475,501]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49F8F83FD360FFC7FE23FE08DC92FE00" box="[499,733,475,502]" country="Thailand" name="Chumphon" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">Chumphon province</collectingRegion>
) and the female of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3C4D5ED360FFC7FC65FE08DA0EFE03" authorityName="Bucsek" authorityYear="2012" box="[949,1089,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Stictane" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="484" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kualabohi">
<emphasis id="B948EACFD360FFC7FC65FE08DA0EFE03" box="[949,1089,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="484">S. kualabohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
